com.facebook.buck.core.model

Interface UnconfiguredBuildTarget

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<UnconfiguredBuildTarget>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractUnconfiguredBuildTarget, ImmutableUnconfiguredBuildTarget

    @ThreadSafe
public interface UnconfiguredBuildTarget
extends Comparable<UnconfiguredBuildTarget>
    Represents a build target without configuration.

    This is indented to be used during early stages of parsing when information about configuration is not available.

      • getCell

        Optional<String> getCell()
        The canonical name of the cell specified in the build target.

        Note that this name can be different from the name specified on the name. See CellPathResolver.getCanonicalCellName(java.nio.file.Path) for more information.

      • getCellPath

        Path getCellPath()
        The path to the root of the cell where this build target is used.

        Note that the same build target name can reference different build targets when used in different cells. For example, given a target name external_cell//lib:target, for a cell that maps external_cell to a cell with location /cells/cell_a, this build target would point to a target //lib:target in the /cells/cell_a cell (defined in a build file located in /cells/cell_a/lib folder. If another cell uses the same build target name, but points external_cell to a different cell, say /cells/cell_b, then this build target refers to a target //lib:target in the /cells/cell_b cell.

      • getBaseName

        String getBaseName()
        Part of build target name the colon excluding cell name.

        For example, for cell//third_party/java/guava:guava this returns //third_party/java/guava.

      • getBasePath

        Path getBasePath()
        The path of the directory where this target is located.

        For example, for //third_party/java/guava:guava this returns Path third_party/java/guava.

      • getShortName

        String getShortName()
        The part of the build target name after the colon.

        For example, for //third_party/java/guava:guava-latest this returns guava-latest.

      • getShortNameAndFlavorPostfix

        String getShortNameAndFlavorPostfix()
        The short name with flavors.

        For example, for //third_party/java/guava:guava-latest#flavor this returns guava-latest#flavor.

      • getFullyQualifiedName

        String getFullyQualifiedName()
        The full name of the build target including the cell name and flavors.

        For example, for cell//third_party/java/guava:guava-latest#flavor this returns cell//third_party/java/guava:guava-latest#flavor.
